column4: hello guys, i got some problem to install pytube. web pages told me to add the link "http://www.bashterritory.com/pytube/releases/ /" to my repository list, but when i reload it, it gave me "GPG error: http://www.bashterritory.com  Release: The following signatures were invalid: NODATA 1 NODATA 2Failed to fetch http://www.bashterritory.com/pytube/releases/Packages.bz2  Sub-process bzip2 returned an error code (2)
Some index files failed to download, they have been ignored, or old ones used instead."
